caption: I like the food.
Great location. It was quite when I got there not a lot of people. Food was great little pricey for silver spring area!

I'm so mad I discovered this place after 3 years since they opened(it's a bit secluded). Luckily they recently joined doordash and found them while looking to try some new places. The food is neat and very flavorful. Highly recommend!
I had the maheberawi at Debab. It included beef spicy and non spicy stew, collard green, cabbage, spicy lentil and kitfo. It was a great sampler of meat and veggies. Quite tasty!

I ordered Debab Mahberawi for Togo, I had mixed grilled beef (not more than 5 to 6 pieces), lamb stew and broiled egg all three stuffed into one of the smaller compartments! please let the your customer know what you have and you don’t in enough amount, so that people make their choices.
First time ordering Ethiopian food and it's pretty amazing. I high recommend ordering from there. The food was that freaking good and the service was great as well.
It's amazing and my favorite Restaurant aroun and sliver spring. So Delicious so nice food and drinking everything is well
Certainly a spot worth stopping by, the food is awesome and well prepared, the rates are fair and it is constantly well organized here. Fantastic work.
This place knows how to treat their clients. Consistently with a welcoming mindset. The food is conveniently priced, constantly flavorful and clean.
Very well kept and accessible restaurant. They offer large meals and for economical prices. I loved the menu very much and the staff were very attentive and informative. Recommended.

Authentic Ethiopian dishes with coffee ceremony! You feel at a typical traditional Ethiopian home: the music, coffee ceremony, traditional food, and the social setting with a feel of friendliness and belongingness during your stay! Ask for "Degfie"  if you pop in there; my most favorite item in Menu!
This spot is worth a visit. They serve big portions for reasonable rates. Always clean and with awesome mood. Will come back again.

This is the best Ethiopian resturant in Meryland. The food portion is too large and the taste is great as well. This is the second time coming to this place & the taste & portion of the food consistent. Friendly service as well. I definitely recommend this place to anyone. I'll be back.
Customer service great
The place serves big dishes and for reasonable prices. super friendly employees. Never disappointing.
They have very texty mixed Ethiopian food.
Delicious food, wonderful service, and a clean, fun, comfortable environment. Overall an excellent experience!

I celebrated my nomination last night in this excellent restaurant. happy to tell that we enjoyed a magnificent evening and the place was unquestionably one of the reasons for this fruitful celebration. The crew  helped in a splendid style, the meals were tasty and my friends were so  overjoyed. We shall definitely visit again for more joyful events. thanks very much.
Great place, the food was amazing and I highly recommend you try this place out. It's certainly worth a try.
Tasty food and very friendly service.
Amazing atmosphere and super affable service. The menu was crisp and delicious. Will surely recommend this restaurant to others. Reasonable rates and large meals. Keep it up.
The house is made amazingly, located on the convenient place. The food is very delicious with different cultural menus.
Great new place...will visit again.
Very authentic Ethiopian Restaurant in the area. The food is very delicious, best customer service!
Everything they make tastes good and there is consistency in the food. Great costumer service and just amazing food.
The food was delicious, proper portion sizes and great value. The servers are very helpful at making suggestions so if you are new to Ethiopian food I would definitely recomend this place.
Lovely and cozy Ethiopian spot.
Nice place for enjoyment with family with delicious Ethiopian food

This place is my favorite place.  Of all restaurants I know I favor it most. I never miss an opportunity to go to this restaurant. everytime  I I need a fair supper, this restaurant comes right away to my mind. fresh and varied  food and a rich cuisine.generous team, and good atmosphere. Also important, the expence is reasonable. I sent my friends to this spot with great pleasure.
They serve large portions and for affordable pricing. very friendly staff members. Fantastic work.
Absolutely a place worth stopping by, the food is awesome and fresh, the rates are fair and it is regularly well kept here. Great work.

Very elegant and accessible restaurant. They offer large meals and for inexpensive rates. We enjoyed the food very much and the staff members were very affable and informative. Will definitely recommend this restaurant.

Just had a terrible experience here. It says you can choose your sides in big letters on the wall but the woman wouldn't let me and chose them for me. And she didn't speak any English so she didn't understand my issue. Beyond ridiculous, I feel like I should get a refund. Also, place is very unappealing, no real ambiance at all. Just poorly run place.
Very good food!  Inexpensive in basic surroundings. Lots of food!  I was very full after eating all of it!
What a delicious food..I really loved it!!

Have been here several times, getting various vegetarian options. All quite good. Compared to fancier Ethiopian restaurants that I've tried, this food has a pizzazz, with each dish having its own personality. Will definitely keep coming back.
I was so hungry, and this place has the best food. I felt like I was being served food by family...the owners are so warm and kind! It has a really friendly and comfortable atmosphere in general.
I love this place, the food is delicious and the atmosphere is perfect.
First time trying Ethiopian food and it was awesome. Everything is seasoned so well, and the portion of food is quite filling.
Test like homemade food,excellent service highly recommended.
Relieves those African food cravings

Used to be really awesome. Great quality and quick service. Seems to have changed some of the recipes and the place just doesn't seem to be running as smoothly any longer. Last few times I've been there the lamb was chewy and the previously delicious split peas have lost much of their flavor. Kind of a bummer, as they were one of my go-tos.

I’m writing this review sitting in ethio express grill after I over ate a bit. I just had to write as soon as possible how amazzzing the food was! Very authentic and delicious!!! The service is great. Definitely one of my favorite place in DMV area!
Great food for the price. All healthy. Great customer service as well.
Cool concept similar to Chipotles in terms of choose your own ingredients. First I've seen in ethio cuisine. Good food tooo
Delicious food, especially the beef ribs. The staff is very friendly and helpful. My family will definitely be back.
Great neighborhood spot, Ethiopian fast casual. Good food, very friendly people.

It's a small place with limited menu options but if you're just starting with Ethiopian food it's easy to dive into. I am not really familiar with all tastes, but for me it was enjoyable. Please note that there is no any parking around except on-street one. The best bet is to park in a Greyhound bus garage.
The food taste delicious. very Good and excellent service .I invest my family member.
It's excellent
Fast a friendly service. Clean and convenient.  Delicious meal... grilled lamb plate with hot lentils, collards and cheese, roasted onions and peppers...yum
Great place to grab a quick bite chipotle style. Lamb is great and there's a nice variety of sides, I recommend the lentils. Atmosphere and staff have always been really nice too
Ethiopian version of Chipotle
It is one of the best Ethiopian restaurants in DMV

Food was very delicious! The set up is similar to a chipotle. Prices are decent. My only complaint .. my food wasn't really hot. My home is only an 8 minute drive from the restaurant and I had to reheat the entire meal!
Tasty overall but saltier than other Ethiopian. Nice interior and large portions.
It's my first time eating at Ethiopia Express Grill. The food is amazing, very large portion and service was excellent. I highly recommend this place especially if you are into vegetarian food.

Fast Ethiopian food that is really good. I've been here one time before the menu changed and waited staff were added. The staff are always friendly and helpful. The only minor problem was that the food was not hot it was warm and still very flavorful.
Great ambience, food and service.

I loved my first visit there! The food was absolutely delicious! Well seasoned and healthy, I felt no guilt about nearly finishing my entire plate. I say nearly because the portion size was great, more than enough for leftovers. The prices are well worth the meal you get! I had the beef combo, which was cooked to order and served hot and fresh! My friend had a vegetarian option, the shirro, and she LOVED IT! Honestly the food can stand well on its own, but the customer service and hospitality made everything so much better! I definitely recommend giving them a try!
A blend of Ethiopian and other native foods served in a Chipotle style.
Delightsome service,delicious Ethiopia cuisine. Best place for Ethiopian food!!!

Overall, I really liked the concept of this restaurant (Chipotle-like, Blaze Pizza-like, Roti-like, Cava-like, etc...).  I would give them a 4.5 because the taste and flavor were there but the foods seemed somewhat more watery than what I'm used to (and I've been to many Ethiopian establishments)...

I miss this place. I used to frequent for lunch when I worked in the area. Although this is more "fast food" oriented they make great food and got me turned onto Ethiopian food. This place has very delicious food, appropriate serving sizes, and good value.

Two stars for cleanliness and cozy environment. By the way I am an Ethiopian who knows Ethiopian food very well and have lived in the united states for two decades to appreciate food from different cultures. But I don't understand what this restaurant is trying to do. It looks like a buffet but Your options are limited. They tell you to pick 1 from here 3 from there and 4 from there. sauces and cheap salads are also among the options. What the hell?  Give me what i want and charge me what you think is fair. Don't limit my options. Being the only Ethiopian express restaurant in the area you are not attracting a lot of Ethiopian customers. A lot of Ethiopians are talking about limited choices, less varieties. If your target is everybody except Ethiopians give them more than lentils and cabbage. Where is Goden tibs, doro wot, Kitfo, alicha, Key, minchet abish, yebeg kikil and more. And please don't be stingy act like a restaurant where there a lot to choose from with a fair price. You can make money and be successful from a lot of traffic. I know it might be tough for you guys because you are surrounded by a lot of Ethiopian restaurants. Find something that make you stand out. I have been to your place not only to eat but also to support but there is always something missing. I can't quiet say what. So may be take a survey. Get ideas from the community and make a radical change. I guarantee you you will see lines in the near future. Today I was not happy with the choices i was given i walked out with out buying. But i will come back. Please take this as a constructive advice not as negative review. Thanks
Food was good. Soda machine was broken. No napkins or toilet paper in the bathroom. Customer service was good.

Our first time trying Ethiopian food and this was a super intro. We loved the injera bread, the grilled beef was so tasty and flavorful. We chose sides that the owner recommended and it was very good. Would come back again definitely!
Stopped for carryout lunch and they only had one carryout box. They were unapologetic that we couldn't get two meals so we just left (they didn't care).
It's like a Chipotle for Ethiopian food. Decent food for the price! The restaurant itself is pretty quiet, seems like a lot of people order using GrubHub. Definitely worth a try.
Great food with options and reasonable price.
Amazing food and service, a piece of Ethiopian beauty
Creative and very delicious Ethiopian food 👌👌👌
Very delicious, but always missing some ingredients for the bowls

I love this place.  The spicy lentils are amazing.  Sadly, they never seem to have the ayib cheese anymore, only feta which is too salty.  They also no longer have green peppers and onions.  The last two times I went there wasn’t any honey yogurt either.  I hope they bring those items back ASAP!
I am a budding vegan and eat here regularly.   It's like an Ethiopian Chipotle. Tasty, healthy and inexpensive.
Very good food.!!
Hmmm, creative! But the food isn’t tasty at all. This ain’t the way I enjoy injera
Was ok but didn't taste authentic
Wow!
Vegan options
Amazing authentic food!

Really clean and orderly. Being African, i can attest to the fact that the food is really amazing. The spices and the greens remind me of my grandmother and mom's cooking. The injera was amazing and really smooth .
Love this place. Fast and tasty

Great  food! Ethiopian fast food, with a method of ordering to streamline the process. I ate there frequently a couple of years ago when I lived in Silver Spring, but since then they've added a service section so you can see the food you're ordering. All of the proteins are good, even the tofu, but I enjoy the lamb the best. And I always get collard greens as one of my 4(!) side dishes. They are deliciously spiced, even for people who don't usually enjoy collards.
Great value for lunch. Tofu option Vegav
Tasty Ethiopian food at a great price.
Great service , real organic food and great hospitality. I love it, they have very reasonable price and great heart to grow.  Go and enjoy it, before it is too late.
Loved it!  Nice tasty selections.

This is a perfect place to sit down and enjoy a delicious ethiopian but the owners take away tip who customers giving from employees,so pls if you give tip,don't do it just give cash to support the employee, this is ridiculous.
Fantastic, top-tier Ethiopian food. Generous portions. I ate for two days off one $10 lunch special.
Great food and huge portions for the price.
It was my first time trying Ethiopian food and it was good! Food were very tasty but we got very thirsty after a couple of hours.

I would give zero ratings the lady who served me did not tell me it was 4 toppings including the cold toppings. I did not want the food and she would not give me my money back. Never going back again.
Fresh food and fast service. Chipotle styled ethiopian restaurant.

Great food! Never expected to see ethiopian food in a chipotle-like fast food environment, but I think it works. There is also a tofu option, so it's vegan friendly, as Ethiopian food usually is! Great place for a quick and healthy fix.

Ethio, but not Express. It took ~9 minutes to wait for any meat to be cooked. BUT! The food is *delicious* and fresh, the portion size is surprisingly filling, and best of all it's in a very accessible environment for those of us who are new to Ethiopian cuisine (forks are provided!).
Seems to cater to the very traditional style and not cozy or fun to wait for food
Best Ethiopian food in the area, generous portions
Amazing fast casual Ethiopian food! Go there!
I walked in five minutes before they were scheduled to close and all the food was already put away. I was excited to try it for the first time, but now I won't be back.
Quick Ethiopian food

Tasty Ethiopian at a great price. It's really hard for me to find single person sized meals of Ethiopian food and this place fits that bill and I still couldn't finish it all! I thought the portions were generous (my plate was overfilling with food). Everything was tasty. The carrots were my favorite. The shiro was a bit under cooked. I will definitely be back if I'm in the area again. Or maybe they should open up a second store in southern Maryland...
I don't remember being here. How good could it really be?
Delicious Ethiopian food, quick. (Served "Chipotle style")
Went for the first time today and the employee serving me was very patient while I figured out what I wanted. Everything was delicious!
Great personal customer service, and Lamb cooked upon ordered. We enjoy eating here at least once a week, and sharing with others. Everything is fresh, and prepared on site.
Overpriced small portions which are not filling. Food was also a little cold.
Quick, friendly and tasty food.

Dish size has been reduced to 75% of what you see on images posted on the internet by prior customers. Served on a black styrofoam 75% versus white cardboard 100%. Size of the injera remains the same, so I used for comparison with other images. I got served on a black styrofoam dish during lunch time. Serving size is only a spoon, thus reduced to 50% of what is shown on the images from their Facebook website. What a disappointment was that the bill also suggested a 20% tip. You end up with 37% of food (compared to what you expect to receive). This equates to paying "$25 to $30" for a meat dish!!! do your math before going...
Very clean and delicious food. Nice change of pace from the  usual Ethiopian restaurant experience.
K NB!

Nice quick option for Ethiopian food.  You choose the meats and sides you want to include in your platter, kind of like chipotle.  Comes with injera or pita.  Price was pretty fair and the food was filling.
Superb!!! Authentic, trendy, super-fast and fair-priced. Will go back again and again and again!!!
Best Ethiopian food around! Everything is fresh!
I love this place!!!! The food is GREAT😋😋😋😋
Great place for lunch.

Note: this review is not about the food, only about the service. I will gladly change this review once the service improves.  We walked in this afternoon, waited for our food for 25 minutes, and when the staff still hadn't started our meal still, asked for a refund. Btw, thanks Manuel at the register for being a good sport about it.  Here's the problem - they had 2 people cooking the food in the back, and only one person actually putting it on plates. The process of actually putting the food on plates takes about 1 minute per plate (I counted), but somehow there's a 5 minute gap between how often different customer's food arrives. What is causing this issue?  This is completely unacceptable, especially for a place with Express in its name. Would serve you well to figure out what is causing this and fix it.
Great idea!
I love the place. ...great food and staff.......

Very happy to introduce my out of town guests to your food. Everyone loved it. I especially like the great variety of vegetarian food. Staff was especially helpful (patient and knowledgeable) when we were all deciding what to order. Clean and pleasant to eat there. Looking forward to coming back soon! thank you.
Great food, clean and bright space. I hope this concept takes off!
Absolutely loved Ethio Express Grill. The first of its kind for Ethiopian restaurant, this place has everything one could hope for.
